replies.body:
A few notes.
Why doesn't {{item:3069}}  build out of {{item:3096}}  and {{item:3114}} ?
The quest it gives isn't really something interesting or on par with {{item:3092}}  and {{item:3401}}

You mean Spellthiefs Edge {{item:3303}} ...

This is Frost Queens Claim {{item:3092}} 

This is Ancient Coin{{item:3301}} 

Upgrades to Talisman of Ascension {{item:3069}} the tier equivalent of FQC...

So if you somehow had a choice between a tier 3 sup item vs a tier 1 I would imagine that wouldnt be much of a choice.

I know this picks on the letter of the topic as opposed to the spirit, but is it really that hard to know what things are called?

{{item:2302}} >{{item:2301}} 
BUT
{{item:3092}} >{{item:3069}} 
This is my opinion, but I feel it can be justified
I build coin when I want to have an extra slot for items, but frost queens when I want to deal some damage
But obviously, you are going to just want to get spelltheifs for the movespeed AND damage
